Steph Curry and LeBron James are at the top of the basketball world — and maybe even the sports world overall. Curry can’t make a move without it being national news. His appearance in a Web.com golf tournament in Hayward got second billing on ESPN’s SportsCenter on Friday night.

James is in contention to be the most recognizable athlete in the world. Of course, both have opposed each other in the last three NBA Finals, and each Finals appearance only increases their collective Q ratings.

However, off the court, Curry and James can snipe at each other, which is actually highly entertaining. Here’s the history of how the two superstars — and their respective teams — have treated each other from a distance.
